      "content": "Even a small amount of alcohol can interact dangerously with diazepam, and the risk outweighs the perceived benefit of a \"boost.\" Alcohol is a depressant, and when combined with a sedative like diazepam, it magnifies drowsiness and can slow your breathing, which is serious. Since you are struggling, the best course of action is to contact your healthcare provider immediately to discuss your sleep difficulties and medication effectiveness. They can adjust your treatment plan safely for you.",
